# API Conventions

## URL Structure

All endpoints are prefixed with `/api/v1` (set in `main.ts`).

```typescript
@Controller("tournaments")  // => /api/v1/tournaments
export class TournamentsController {}
```

## Authentication

Routes require JWT by default. Use `@Public()` for unauthenticated access:

```typescript
import { Public } from "../common/decorators/public.decorator";

@Get("health")
@Public()  // No JWT required
healthCheck() {}

@Get("profile")  // JWT required (default)
getProfile() {}
```

## Request Validation

Use DTOs with class-validator decorators:

```typescript
export class CreateTournamentDto {
  @IsString()
  @MinLength(3)
  name: string;

  @IsInt()
  @Min(2)
  @Max(10)
  max_players: number;

  @IsOptional()
  @IsDateString()
  scheduled_start_at?: string;
}
```

## Response Format

**Success:**
```typescript
return { id: entity.id, ...data };  // 200/201
```

**Errors:**
```typescript
throw new NotFoundException("Tournament not found");
throw new BadRequestException("Invalid bet amount");
throw new UnauthorizedException("Invalid credentials");
throw new ConflictException("Bot already registered");
```

## Controller Responsibilities

Controllers handle:
- Request/response transformation
- HTTP status codes
- Route decorators

Controllers do NOT contain business logic — delegate to services.
